b'Today\xe2\x80\x99s world is facing a number of challenges. How we all come together as a community will make a difference in moving forward. I want to thank @TheEconomicClub and David Rubenstein for yesterday\xe2\x80\x99s conversation. https://t.co/yTUasdADOs'

b'I\xe2\x80\x99m so proud to see the Nasdaq team around the world rise to the occasion. We\xe2\x80\x99re looking out for each other and we\xe2\x80\x99re continuing to get the job done for all of you who rely on us. https://t.co/bVjqTZ7jEr'

b'Our economy and country is resilient. We have proven that before. We will get to the other side by playing our part. Follow the advice of health professionals, practice social distancing, #flattenthecurve. If we do this right the first time, we\xe2\x80\x99ll have a faster recovery.'
b'My advice for the future? Plan for everything. Our risk group thinks through situations so that our organization is fully prepared and we are able to keep our people safe.'
b'As @ScottWapnerCNBC mentioned @Nasdaq has pledged business and philanthropic support in response to COVID-19 \nhttps://t.co/6iimRodoiQ https://t.co/NyDbXWAd25'

b'It\xe2\x80\x99s impossible to prepare for a crisis of this scope and scale, but I am very proud of my team. They\xe2\x80\x99ve stayed ahead of the curve as we\xe2\x80\x99ve managed this crisis across 30 countries.'

b'All leaders are facing incredible challenges \xe2\x80\x93 managing both large and small workforces and operations. I have been talking with our clients and financial institutions and it\xe2\x80\x99s positive to hear that many are operating work from home policies.'

b'I also think there are aspects that will stay the same. People love experiences - they love to travel, they love restaurants and they love connections. Our society will go back to those things as soon as we are able.'

b'I believe there will be lasting effects just like there were after 9/11, Hurricane Sandy and the credit crisis. We\xe2\x80\x99ve come away from those situations as a stronger business and a stronger nation.'

b'@Nasdaq was built by a networked community of investors and traders. We\xe2\x80\x99re very proud that we\xe2\x80\x99ve always been able to operate markets remotely. We\xe2\x80\x99ve constantly invested in technology and our people, so that we\xe2\x80\x99re prepared to maintain our markets through a moment like this.'
b'For my executive team and myself, our focus is on the health and well-being of our people. Early on we implemented critical visitor and work from home policies, as well as split team logistics.'
b'That way, when we make it through this, they can start to reemploy and staff their businesses again.'

b'This is a global health crisis. Everyone and business is facing massive disruption and no small business, publicly-listed company or government is solely responsible. Washington needs to pass the #StimulusBill as quickly as possible, so businesses get the liquidity they require.'
